    "feat": {
        "name": "Orchard's Endurance",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "Patches of bark appear on the skin of you and your nearby allies. You and your allies in your kinetic aura gain resistance 5 to bludgeoning and piercing damage. In addition, you and your affected allies roll flat checks to recover from persistent damage twice and take the higher result; this is a fortune effect.\n\n---\n\n**Level (+4)** The resistance increases by 2.",
        "level": 14,
        "action_type": {
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "name": "One Action"
        },
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Impulse",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 15,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f83779b12b3f1e7096ae9a32ca68ea4f",
                "text": "The primary magical actions kineticists use are called impulses. You can use an impulse only if your kinetic aura is active and channeling that element, and only if you have a hand free to shape the elemental flow. The impulse trait means the action has the concentrate trait unless another ability changes this. If an impulse allows you to choose an element, you can choose any element you're channeling, and the impulse gains that element's trait.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "concentrate",
                        "alt": "concentrate",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Kineticist",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 237,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "721afce0c1e219e9edd3709db105bb4e",
                "text": "This indicates abilities from the kineticist class.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "kineticist",
                        "alt": "kineticist",
                        "game-obj": "Classes",
                        "aonid": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Plant",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 125,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 459,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "651e06f09e5aea780d7c70a36ce5b1f2",
                "text": "Vegetable creatures have the plant trait. They are distinct from normal plants. Magical effects with this trait manipulate or conjure plants or plant matter in some way. Effects that manipulate plants have no effect in an area with no plants."
            },
            {
                "name": "Primal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 134,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 460,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic."
            },
            {
                "name": "Stance",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 152,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 139",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 139",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 139,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9035508c239ef7305f5fce73844742d8",
                "text": "A stance is a general combat strategy that you enter by using an action with the stance trait, and you remain in for some time. A stance lasts until you get knocked out, until its requirements (if any) are violated, until the encounter ends, or until you use a stance action again, whichever comes first. After you take an action with the stance trait, you can\u2019t take another one for 1 round. You can enter or be in a stance only in encounter mode. You can Dismiss a stance."
            },
            {
                "name": "Wood",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 463,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "7c548a9e0a2647c082989720b3de0a87",
                "text": "Effects with the wood trait conjure or manipulate wood. Those that manipulate wood have no effect in an area without wood. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of wood or have a connection to magical wood.  \n  \nThese planes consist of trees and other flora latticed in organic patterns. Wood planes are often perfectly constructed to match their desired purpose or environment but aren\u2019t usually outright hostile to visitors."
            }
        ],
